article.headline: Youngstown State 72, James Madison 65
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Quin Humphrey had 24 points, Domonique Crawford scored all 20 of his points in the second half and Youngstown State rallied from 18 down to defeat James Madison 72-65 Wednesday night. Crawford went 8-of-10 from the floor in the second half and provided more than half the Penguins' points in a game-changing 30-8 surge that lasted 11 minutes. Crawford's 18 points during the run helped Youngstown State (3-6) turn a 47-29 deficit into a 59-55 lead with 4:11 to play. Crawford, who didn't take a shot in the first half while playing only four minutes, added two free throws with 3:03 left for his final points. Humphrey, who also had nine rebounds, made 3-of-4 free throws and a dunk in the final 39 seconds after the Dukes (2-5) had closed to 65-63. He finished 12-of-14 at the foul line. Cavell Johnson led James Madison with 25 points. Daniel Freeman scored 15 and Juwann James had 13 points and 12 rebounds.
